raw_entry:
BENJAMIN WOOD, 400 acs. (N.
L.), King Wm, Co; on S. side of Mattapony Riv., & on S, side the South River;
20 Feb. 1719, p. 3. Adj. Arthur Smith;
& Robert Jones. 40 Shill.

JAMES BRIDGFORTH, 400 acs. (N.
L.), K. & Q. Co., in St. Stephen’s Par;
on N. side of Mattapony Riv., & on
roth sides of a br. of Warner's River;
adj, Nathaniel Sanders & Thomas Chew;
20 Feb. 1719, p. 7. 40 Shill.

JOHN KING, 97 acs. (N. L.), Pr.
Geo. Co; on S. side of Nottoway Riv;
at the first falls above Sturgion Run;
17 Aug. 1720, p. 39. 10 Shill.

JOHN GUN, 150 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on N. side of James River;
17 Aug. 1720, p. 44. 15 Shill.

STEPHEN CHASTAIN, 37 acs. (N.
L.), Henrico Co; within bounds of the
land laid out for the French Refugees;
adj. Peter Dutoi; down James River;
17 Aug. 1720, p. 46. 5 Shill.

PHILLIP TODD, of K. & Q. Co;
400 acs. (N. L.), King Wm. Co., in St.
John’s Par; ber. Polecat Sw. & the
Reedy Sw; adj. Geo. Duglass; Richard
Crosha Walker; & Thomas Carr, Junr;
21 Feb, 1720, p. 52. 40 Shill.

HENRY WYCHE, 370 acs. (N. L.),
Surry Co; on N.. side of Maherin Riv;
cor. of Robert Hix; by the Miery Br;
22 June 1722, p. 101. 30 Shill, &
Imp. of 2 pers: Thomas Brown &
Catherine Brown.

DRURY OLIVER, of Henrico Co;
300 acs. (N. L.), Pr. Geo. Co; on head
of Hatcher’s Run; adj. John Bannister;
crossing forks of the Flatt Br; 22 June
1722, p. 118. 30 Shill.

JAMES HOLEMAN, 400 acs. (N.
L.), Henrico Co; N. side of James Riv;
on E. side of the Dear Pen Br; along
Evans’ line; & Russell & Clark’s line;
18 Feb. 1722, p. 159. 40 Shill,

ARTHUR KAVENAUGH, of Surry
Co; 50 acs. (N. L.), Is. of Wight Co;
S. side of Maherin Riv. & on E. side
of the Great Swamp; adj, his own land;
& Adam Ivy; 18 Feb. 1722, p. 171. 5
Shill.

JOHN PASMORE, 100 acs. (N. L.),
Surry Co; on S, side of Nottoway Riv;
on his own land; by the Island Swamp;
18 Feb. 1722, p. 182. Imp. of 2 pers:
Benjamin Chaficey & William Tilly.

GEORGE REIVES, 235 acs. (N. L.),
Surry Co; on S, side of Nottoway River;
18 Feb. 1722, p. 192. 25 Shill.

HOWEL EDMONDS, of Surry Co;
485 acs. (N. L.), Pr. Geo. Co; on both
sides of the gr. creek of Meherin Riv;
below the Settlement; 5 Sept. 1723. p.
214. 50 Shill.

HENRY BOW, 200 acs. (N. L.),
Hanover Co; on brs, of Crump’s Creek;
5 Sept. 1723, p. 222. 20 Shill,

JOHN VAWTER, 25 A., 92 Per.,
(N. L.), Essex Co., in St. Ann’s Par;
on §. side of Rappa. Riv; in the fork
of Blackburn’s Cr; adj. Thomas Page;
5 Sept. 1723, p. 233. 5 Shill.

JOSEPH MAYO, 300 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on S. side of James River;
adj. his own, & land of Joseph Hooper;
5 Sept. 1723, p. 238. 30 Shill.

HENRY CLAY, 400 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on S, side of Swift Cr;
at the mouth of Ephriam Lile’s branch;
on James Eakin’s line; 5 Sept. 1723, p.
241. 40 Shill.

JOHN QUARLES, 417 acs. (N. L.),
Spotsylvania Co., in St. George’s Par;
on Nussaponnack Runn; adj, William
Hansford; Mott’s patent; James Canney;
& Francis Thornton; 30 Sept. 1723, p.
288. 45 Shill.

ABRAHAM FIELD, 800 acs. (N.
L.), Spotsyl. Co., in St. George’s Par;
in the fork of Rappa. River; on N. side
of Flat Run, in line of William Skrine;
to the Mountain Run; 5 Oct. 1723, p.
288. 4 Lbs. Money.

JOHN WELCH, 400 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on N: side of Swift Cr;
on W. side of the main br. of Tomahake; on Mr, Alexander Marshal's line;
20 Feb, 1723, p. 309. 40 Shill,

LEWIS GREEN, of Pr. Geo. Co; 135
acs, (N. L.), Surry Co; on S. side of
Nottoway River; adj. Ephraim Parham;
by the Flat Swamp; by the High Hills;
20 Feb, 1723, p. 311. 15 Shill.

EDWARD YARBROUGH & WILLIAM YARBROUGH, 400 acs. (N.
L.), King Wm. Co., in St. John’s Par;
on W. side of Long Branch; on Robert
Baber; & William Cockerham’s line;
20 Feb. 1723, p. 330. 40 Shill.

JOHN SMITH, JUNR., 150 acs. (N.
L.), in Up. Par. of Nansemond Co;
adj. William Sumner, on Bennet’s Cr;
& Epaphroditus Moore; 20 Feb. 1723,
Pp. 338.
